                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Nikis fils de Ph<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Nikis son of Ph<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Nikis figlio di Ph<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>As pointed by J.M. Reynolds, no Nikis is up to now known in association with a name beginning with a phi. No restoration of the father's name can thus be suggested.</p>
